						<summary>

						<p>This is also damaged. It records a gift of 5 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> probably by the same donor mentioned above, who is called Poṅṉuḍaiyāṉ Iḷaṉgoṇḍi and is stated to have been a <hi rend="italic">Vēḷaikkāṟa</hi> (body-guard) of the king. This amount is said to represent one fourth of the cost of burning a full lamp and to supplement his previous gift, to make it a full one.</p>						

